data.content:
Wait — `JsonSerializer.Serialize(writer, error, typeof(ResponseError), s_options)` — is the `Serialize(Utf8JsonWriter, object?, Type, JsonSerializerOptions)` overload annotated? Let me check. In .NET 9, `JsonSerializer.Serialize(Utf8JsonWriter, object?, Type, JsonSerializerOptions)` IS annotated with `[RequiresUnreferencedCode]`. 

The only truly AOT-safe overloads are those taking `JsonTypeInfo`. So I need:

```csharp
JsonSerializer.Serialize(writer, error, (JsonTypeInfo<ResponseError>)s_options.GetTypeInfo(typeof(ResponseError)));
JsonSerializer.Deserialize(json, (JsonTypeInfo<ResponseError>)s_options.GetTypeInfo(typeof(ResponseError)));
```

